  "metaTitle": "Hiring From a Competitor: Onboarding Without Inheriting a Lawsuit &mdash; Tom Cedoz",
  "metaDescription": "A checklist for hiring a candidate who is leaving a competitor without importing a trade-secret or breach-of-covenant suit: diligence on covenants, a written no-documents rule before day one, and a clean onboarding record.",
  "standfirst": "When a new hire&rsquo;s former employer sues, the new employer is usually named alongside the employee &mdash; often as the deeper pocket. The exposure is rarely the hire itself; it is what the hire brings, copies, or solicits in the first weeks. Almost all of that is preventable, and most of it has to be prevented before the start date.",
  "docMetaItems": [
    "Updated June 2026",
